    <p>To mark the Mid-Au­tumn Fes­ti­val, mas­ter ch chef Lap Fai of Hua Ting Restau­rant at O Or­chard Ho­tel Sin­ga­pore has cre­ated a se se­lec­tion of healthy moon­cakes. New th this year is the Sour Plum with Roasted O Or­ganic Hazel­nut snowskin moon­cake ($ ($70 for a box of eight) that com­bines st steamed and ground sour plums with ro roasted or­ganic Turk­ish hazel­nuts. If you lik like a dash of al­co­hol in your moon­cakes, th the White Lo­tus Paste with Cham­pagne G Ganache snowskin moon­cake ($70 for a box of eight) will de­light with its decadent champ cham­pagne-filled white choco­late ganac ganache and Hua Ting’s white lo­tus paste, wh while the Blue­berry with Vin­tage Hua Diao Wine snowskin moon­cake ($70 for a box of eight) is a treat with its del­i­cate bal­ance of sweet and tart blue­ber­ries in­fused with vin­tage rice wine.</p>
